snippet: With its debut on Monday, MundoFox, a partnership between Fox and a Colombian television company, will enter a market long dominated by Univision and Telemundo.
abstract: Spanish-language network MundoFox, partnership between News Corp's Fox International Channels and RCN Television in Colombia, makes its debut in 50 cities in the United States; it will enter market long dominated by Univision and Telemundo.
lead_paragraph: With its debut on Monday, MundoFox, a partnership between Fox and a Colombian television company, will enter a market long dominated by Univision and Telemundo.

headline.seo: MundoFox, New Spanish-Language Network, to Make Debut
headline.main: MundoFox to Enter the Latino TV Market
headline.print_headline: MundoFox To Enter The Latino TV Market
